   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "overhead-kidney",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from qiskit import *\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization import plot_distribution, plot_error_map\n",
    "from qiskit.providers.fake_provider import FakeHanoi\n",
    "\n",
    "from qiskit_ibm_provider import IBMProvider\n",
    "\n",
    "from qiskit_aer import AerSimulator\n",
    "from qiskit_aer.noise import (NoiseModel, ReadoutError,\n",
    "                              depolarizing_error, thermal_relaxation_error)\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "further-unemployment",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 929.397x385.28 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "a = '1111'\n",
    "nq = len(a)+1\n",
    "\n",
    "bv = QuantumCircuit(nq, nq-1)\n",
    "bv.x(nq-1)\n",
    "bv.h(range(nq))\n",
    "bv.barrier()\n",
    "bv.cx(range(len(a)), nq-1)\n",
    "bv.barrier()\n",
    "bv.h(range(nq))\n",
    "bv.barrier()\n",
    "bv.measure(range(nq-1), range(nq-1))\n",
    "\n",
    "bv.draw('mpl')"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "differential-fitness",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Readout error"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "mobile-puppy",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 779.079x385.28 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ghz = QuantumCircuit(5)\n",
    "ghz.h(0)\n",
    "ghz.cx(0, range(1, 5))\n",
    "ghz.measure_all()\n",
    "ghz.draw('mpl')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "residential-magic",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Parameters \n",
    ": a list of assignment probability vectors $P(A|B)$ where $A$ and $B$ are noisy measurement outcomes and true measurement oucomes, respectively.  \n",
    "Explicitly, $P(A|B)= [P(A|k)]$ where $k\\in\\{0, 1, 2, ..., 2^n - 1\\}$ for $n$ number of qubits.\n",
    "\n",
    "    E.g. for 1 qubit case, $P(A|B) = [P(A|0), P(A|1)] = [[P(0|0), P(1|0)], [P(0|1), P(1|1)]]$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "regulated-brunei",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "p10, p01 = 0.01, 0.03\n",
    "ro = ReadoutError([[1-p10, p10],[p01, 1-p01]])\n",
    "\n",
    "meas_noise = NoiseModel()\n",
    "meas_noise.add_all_qubit_readout_error(ro)\n",
    "#meas_noise.add_readout_error(ro,[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "right-commercial",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "noiseSim = AerSimulator(noise_model=meas_noise)\n",
    "\n",
    "ghz_trans = transpile(ghz, noiseSim)\n",
    "counts_ghz = noiseSim.run(ghz_trans, shots=100000).result().get_counts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "funded-steam",

    }

   ]

    "err_cx = depol_cx.compose(thermal_cx)\n",

    "print(err_cx)"
